The aircraft to monitor people are increasingly sought by the parents to monitor their children.
The fear for their child brings more people to think about the monitor through a GPS.
system, introduced at the beginning to find cars can also be used to trace the movement of people and help for some cases such exmple that of the small Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently too great a box of matches but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of the small Anicka moved a large number of people and they have begun to seek ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
. " We are trying to tell everyone that it is not spying but only an alternative to reduce the likelihood of another tragedy, " said Petr Pilin society MAcro Weil is one of the suppliers of tracking devices on the market.
" I confess that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet met such cases ."
" The majority of people are clients who really buy the product for security reasons, said Pilin.
According to the children should always knowing what is used " box " and how the emergency.
The child psychologist, Dana Bockova, drew attention if the child does not want to be on something of this type, débarassera.
'Et even the smallest can demonstrate a great creativity when it comes to rid express something when they do not want to be in control.
" The phones, which can be cut as they trace, have already led parents to long delays, " says Bockova.
According to it, the fact that this type of system can assist in case of aggression is very questionable.
" If it is a kidnapping prepared, the author will ensure that the child has no electronic device which could locate ."
" Today, it is the phone ."
" Once will develop devices, they (criminals) will seek them because the sale will be supported by advertising campaign ."
" In such cases criminals will always be ahead of the police, " said psychologist.
She admits that such aircraft can help during an attack not prepared by a paedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, which offers trace both cars and people, claims to have this type of device can help, even if it was destroyed in the case of an attack.
" The aircraft can be paramétré so it emission régulière after a period of time ."
" In the case where the aircraft is destroyed, it remains the final position of the person concerned ."
' more expensive aircraft were also a inclinomètre immediately reported the position of the person who had slipped and in the position extended nothing ', said Cech.
According to the phones so-called intelligent are equipped with a navigation system can propose a similar service after formatting with a prologiciel Special.
tracking systems problem today is that it is either a system similar to those in pendentif the size of a box of matches or the smaller telephones.
It may still lose.
According to Pilina of Macro Weil, which is why the tests are being conducted to make aircraft which resemble common digital watches.
" will be the advantage that the potential aggressor cannot recognize tracing system ."
" Or he realizes after some time, given the police more time ," he adds.
What tracing system is developed in the form of bracelet or pendentif, it utilisiera always the same technology to trace of cars.
It is a combination of acquisition systems to a position of GPS (which is currently used in autonavigation) and a mobile phone to alert the current position of a vehicle.
