The group Fujitsu relocates its subsidiary of Bad Homburg to Frankfurt.
The next year in July, 400 staff will transfer to Astro Park their place of work, which is currently in the office building of the Place Mareinbader Bad Homburg in the region.
The Japanese group Fujitsu relocates its branch of Bad Homburg in Frankfurt.
said Wednesday the giant specializing in the manufacture and maintenance of computers next year in July, the workplace of 400 men and women, so far on the place Marienbader town of Bad Homburg, will be transferred to Astro Park, vast complex of offices located on the street Lyoner Straße Headquarters Niederrad of Frankfurt.
