The first step in the production is quite simple.
Luciano provides the basic ingredients, such as milk, cream, milk powder, sugar and stabilisers in a large mixing that fuel to 85 degrees through an electronic programme, and cools immediately to four degrees.
It then held a valve installed on the machine: it is a basic white cream pasteurized, the foundation of all kinds of ice in milk.
The trainer was besieged with question: Is it possible to manufacture ice using only natural substances without stabilising?
How can we give free rein to the personal pleasure of experimentation?
Mr. Luciano cautioned against being mislead by the spirit of the time.
Anyone who does that ice made from natural ingredients, perhaps despite it used stabilisers: a natural product, for example flour bean guar obtained from the beans of guar.
It is obviously possible to manufacture ice without using stabilizing, only must sell within 24 hours, otherwise it collapses and the customer does not croquera nothing other than pellets of ice.
