There are reports that the chairman of the group of experts Efsa for genetically modified plants, Mr. Harry Kuiper, as well as other experts Efsa are under contract with the pressure group Ilsi.
The latter is funded by groups such as Monsanto, Nestlé or Bayer.
Mr. Kuiper worked a determining factor in the development of test requirements of the Efsa for genetically modified plants and is, therefore, clearly in a situation of conflict of interest, according to the criticism made by Mr. Then.
requirements developed are letter by paragraphs, the positions of the pressure group Ilsi and are thus marks of the industry which, basically, would be monitored by the authorities based in Parma, Italy.
It is the second time that Testbiotech a conflict of interest.
