The agency sees itself as a neutral forum bringing together experts from, among others, science, industry and politics in order to assess the risks of biotechnology without being in the pay of a lobby.
In this case, the independent experts such as Mr Then resent the fact that genetically modified crops would be accepted without any test food animals, and that it was not tested the impact of these plants on the environment.
