The lion is ready to be ashamed of, the restructuring of GMMs no longer expected that the final green light for the court
After 18 months of turmoil and uncertainty, GMMs finally got the green light to begin to zero.
A federal bankruptcy judge in New York, was officially hired Thursday, the plan pré-emballés " by the creditors that approximately $5 billion of debt would be wiped out; paving the way for the entertainment business, with 86 years of existence, to concentrate its efforts on the production and distribution of films and TV shows.
With the decision Thursday, according to which the plan meets the requirements of the bankruptcy code of the United States, no legal obstacles remain before GMMs to stay afloat under the guardianship of the founders of Entertainment Spyglass, Gary Barber and Roger Birnbaum, who will become the Directors-General of what will be a studio eased.
The staff will be reduced to approximately 320 on 400.
GMMs will not really Chapter 11 as JPMorgan Chase has not reached a credit facility of $500 million to finance the new operations and production of GMMs.
It is being distributed under licence by the investment bank, which has itself to $75 million, and should be financed by mid-December.
The studio restructuring process began in May 2009 when the investment bank Moelis& Co. , has been committed to advise the direction on how to put its finances as it did not have the means to pay the interest amounting to $300 million a year.
In August, the director general, Harry he was replaced by Stephen Cooper, a former CEO of Enron and an expert in recovery, known for his work in Krispy Kreme Doughnuts.
Attempts to Moelis and Cooper to resolve the financial difficulties of GMMs and meet more than 140 creditors of studio have taken much more time than expected.
After several months of discussions, the parties have agreed, by the end of 2009, to put the company up for sale.
however, the auction has attracted few bidders which none of them was willing to pay $2 billion more for creditors were seeking.
In the spring of this year, again while the GMMs team had started working on a restructuring plan which, after months of internal disagreements and debates, has finally been approved by creditors at the end of October.
When GMMs fate officially bankruptcy in the following weeks, companies Moelis and Cooper receive bonuses of several million dollars for their work.
Moelis& Co. , which has already received $1.2 million, will receive a payment of $9.5 million.
Cooper enterprises, which raised $375 per month for their leadership of the company, will receive a bonus of success " of $4 million.
Barber and Birnbaum account revive GMMs production, which is released only one movie this year, and put up a list of seven or eight films come from 2012.
They also intend to co-financing two movies based on " Hobbit ," with Warner Bros.
The studio must conclude a separate loan of $265 million and $275 million to fund its share of these two films, which must be done by Peter Jackson.
The investor Carl Icahn, which holds about 18 per cent of the debt of GMMs, has tried to achieve a merger of studio with Lions Gate Entertainment, where he is the principal shareholder.
However, recent discussions between the two companies had not led to an agreement.
