The police and the Federal Security Service are enormous racketeering that help explain the high cost of living in Moscow, he said.
They have the money not only of legitimate companies but also of organized criminal groups.
Each layer of bureaucracy - the Prime Minister Vladimir Putin called the " vertical of power " - takes its share money ensue towards the top of the scale.
The note, which was sent to Washington as the Ambassador John Beyrle, was posted Wednesday by Wikileaks on its Web site.
The note is based on sources whose names have been removed.
It was written when Yuri Luzhkov was still mayor of Moscow; and it is largely responsible for corruption.
It was dismissed in October by President Dmitry Medvedev but there has since been few traces of cleansing.
Luzhkov and his wife, Elena Batourina, who owns a construction company, have always denied the accusations of corruption over the years; and he has won many defamation trial on those charges.
