Zapatero and the German red line
Berlin has opted to stay with the euro, but it establishes the conditions throughout the Union.
Tensions markets have led to a doble government response.
On the one hand, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero announced new methods of adjustment, which vary from tax cuts for the PMEs, regulation of private placement agencies or removal of 426 aid for the unemployed without professional contribution to the privatisation of 49 per cent of AENA, airport management Barajas and El Prat and 30 per cent of Loteries of the State.
On the other, the Vice-President Elena Salgado, with the support of former President Felipe González, criticism of Chancellor Angela Merkel's responsibility to detach the current crisis.
How should we interpret these movements?
It should be mentioned that the position of Merkel is not a mistake in its forthcoming policy.
On the contrary, it is another restriction of the difficult process of redefinition of the euro.
And Germany has a radically new vision of his future, which shocked with maintaining the old traditions of most of its partners.
Given the European resistance, in Germany began to speculate on the three possible exit to the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, by itself, Austria and the Netherlands, among others, and the south would abandon the monetary zone.
The second, the recovery of Mark, although now it seems of science fiction, with a favourable opinion, almost a 50 per cent of the population.
The third, a new approach to the euro, in line with the German proposals for greater control macroeconomic budgetary rigour, fines on countries that infringe, possible suspensions of payments and the private sector expansion potential costs of adjustments.
The German position is clear and that is that it is therefore now there is no place for an apology.
First, in 2009, when the IMF as the European Commission stimulated the deficits, the German Government has invented a constitutional reform to prevent them from 2016.
This was the first signal of difference between what Germany believed that we should make (plans fiscal rigour and stability of public finances and its European partners, ci-inclut France.
The second of Central was when Merkel has barely extended the decision saved Greece.
From the moment -là it was the subject of a fierce criticism, but the truth is that the political consensus in Germany and the public opinion and the published were against the rescue of Greece.
Finally, towards the end of October, Merkel reiterated a clear position, in calling for the reform of the European treaties in order to make possible the rescue of a country, and at the same time to private lenders to bear a share of the cost.
This has been interpreted as anti-European, because it precipitated the crisis in Ireland and the rest.
But its proposal, although a toned down, has been approved and, the following month, we should attend the process of reform of the Union which is possible these measures from 2013.
Germany has charted a red line that she did not think cross.
And it said that, although now it must take measures with which we may not be too much agreement, from that date the former functioning of the euro would end.
2013 will mean the creation of a new currency area, in which the countries that break the rules will be severely punished, they may be forced to be declared in default and, in this case -là, the private sector will also cost advantage.
Germany we said that we must follow a strict path of growth with high rates of savings and investment, moderation in consumption, improvements in productivity and competitiveness and positive external balances.
An alternative based on debt and the construction, with huge holes in the balance of payments, such as those who chaired the Spanish growth in the boom years, will simply not be tolerated.
The development is clear.
And it would be difficult not to hear.
It is not only to extend the budget deficit to 3 per cent in 2013.
What we demand is much harder.
And it must absolutely not do in these circumstances is to deceive ourselves.
I hope that the current turbulence are coming to us tranquillity.
And knowing seize the opportunity that has been given until spring 2013.
It seems that President Zapatero also heard this form and its dual statement (promised reforms after the meeting of the past Saturday with big business and the announcement yesterday of new measures) suggests that, despite the criticism of Merkel, opened the way to the thesis that it must be in the house.
But the red line that Germany has mapped out is there, and they seem to move.
among the possibilities that, we cannot exclude that abandoning a monetary area too packed with less serious.
