Sport and fraud law
The tricks similar to that of Alonso and Ramos against Ajax demonstrate the ingenuity but not escape punishment.
The expulsion hatched in principle by two players of Real Madrid (Xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) for the 23 November match against Ajax in the Champions League has caused much ink on the nature anti-sportif such behaviour and if the two players should be punished by UEFA.
As is well known, a few minutes before the conclusion of the match (that their team already earned clearly -RRB - the two players have deliberately lost the time when they have been negligent to determine the arbitrator of the second yellow card.
Thus, and as Real Madrid will eventually be leader of his group, the two players with the regulatory sanction for the next match match barrage against Auxerre and can pass without boxes to the next phase.
Finally, the disciplinary committee of UEFA has punished with two matches of the team coach, José Mourinho and are economic players involved.
The provocation of a yellow card in circumstances such as plate or similar is not new, but rather in the world of football.
It is so widespread that it is part of the ethos of non-écrites, but followed, of the sport.
Part of the debate in the case reflected at the fact that this has been leading a team of Real Madrid's entity (which in its anthem is the nobility and the honour and that in the past occasions has fined its players for similar acts) and the dramatization orchestrated, apparently, by Mourinho, which adds an episode of its dilatée history of technician histrionique and provocative.
In any event, the debate whether this type of behaviour not expressly prohibited by the settlement contradicts the principles of sport, i.e., if with these actions have made a fraud; because, in effect, they are friendly with the sport, but seem to avoid.
will consider the type of damage they cause to the spirit of sport.
A property that includes sportsmanship is the physical integrity of opposing players, an aspect that with these actions had not been put in danger, that is, there has not been a violent game.
Another property to be referred to the game right is the team of players offenders would an unjust for the team, which is not the case.
however, the absurd of players of Real Madrid is that it is not what is normally characterised as cheating o fraud of the law, because its violation of rules has not been conducted in secret to try to avoid the penalty, but has tried to be as clear as possible to receive the criminalization of the referee.
They were waiting and they have gladly accepted the punishment.
Another issue is the kind of advantage that the offenders are considered willful misconduct.
Here it seems necessary to note that we are not in a situation of disadvantage to rival and is an advantage in the same match either, because obviously the result of the action involves leaving their own team with players.
And this is not a useful strategy for the next match either, because the club could not count on these players.
Obviously the advantage lies in the fact that the players begin the next phase of the Champions League without boxes that can threaten their participation in a future match.
but it is a long-term benefit, with a degree of uncertainty because the team could be eliminated to and from that, with this action the players are doing a match penalty and spend the second cycle of boxes, in which the suspension due to the accumulation of boxes with a less than in the first round.
So, ladder, it is not clear that this is an advantage.
Ultimately, these actions are not contrary to the spirit of sport, which is still part strategic decision-making that promote the use of rules allow.
In our case, the players were not activated to avoid the application of the penalty (it would be a clear case of fraud law -RRB - m otherwise they chose the moment in which they are subjected to it.
They made a strategic decision without thwart the penalty or flee the -là.
Even if the border between Engineering and fraud is, in this opportunity I think was a clear case of engineering.
The controversy, I believe, is because of two factors: because there were two auto-expulsions and conveying the guidelines for the cause.
The harm to the principles of sport by these actions is not as much ethical as aesthetic.
