China maintains the objectives of reducing greenhouse gases
The representative in the COP16 assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and has detailed maintains its offer to reduce until 2020 between 40 and 45 per cent its emissions of greenhouse gases.
China maintains its offer to reduce between 40 and 45 percent its emissions of greenhouse gases by 2020, Su Wei, representative of the COP16.
In his first public appearance in the 16th Conference of the Parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on the Change (COP16 -RRB - Su Wei was assured that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce the trace of coal and redeploy its industry.
In fact, outlined, the last four years had switched to $245 million in the efforts to reduce the emission of greenhouse gases.
, however, it has clearly stated that China will not change its objectives, but it will continue to work together with the international community in this area.
He mentioned that the Chinese strategy in the field of climate change is divided into four areas: dialogue; construction of capacity; construction of institutions and support pilot programmes.
There has been progress in all these areas, ci-inclut approval last year of a new Energy Act, which recognizes the raised regarding the reduction of greenhouse gases, explained.
On the other hand, he pointed out that in China, federal authorities have worked in a coordinated manner with the government and local to achieve the objectives of energy savings, efficient energy use and cut emissions.
In addition, has said, there are various plans or completed, both funded by the Chinese government and by the governments of other countries.
For example, mentioned the Programme of Use Efficiente of Energy, which has been implemented in the last five years and which has received investment of the United Nations -RRB - the Government and private initiative.
There is also a draft provincial of climate change, another change light bulbs by energy-efficient lamps and another for mitigation and adaptation, has detailed.
at the same table, Martin Krol, scientific adviser to the government of that country regarding climate change, provided that the efforts of China have been larger what we think.
For example, outlined, the per capita emissions of greenhouse gases in China is three tons per person, while the United States is 100 tons; China is responsible for 9 per cent of the historic contribution in the contamination.
Similarly, it has made unprecedented efforts in the use of energy, how we can increase a 20% energy efficiency in the last five years and provides another similar to 2020, said.
