The European Union change the rules for the visa
People must go to the Visa seekers before their interview in the Section Consulaire; the cost the waiting time is diminished.
From 10 January 2011 processing visas at the embassy and consulates of United States change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants will have to submit to the seekers of Visa (ASC, according to its acronyms in English) before their interview in the Section Consulaire.
The CSA will take the biometric information from the applicant, which will be reviewed by the Section Consulaire before the interview.
The new procedure will launch some benefits for candidates, including the following:
The total cost to deal with the visa will be lower, there would be no need to make a payment for an appointment, another payment for the treatment of visa and another for the mail service delivers the document.
The aspiring will conduct a single payment covering the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 in the case of visas for (ci-inclut visas for temporary workers) and $390 for visas of traders and investors.
persons wishing to renew their visas will not submit to an interview with Representative Consulaire, they will only to the CSA nearest where they will present the documents and we take their fingerprints.
At because the biometric information will be made in the CSA, seeking a second event to be interviewed in the Section Consulaire remain less time than before.
Similarly, visa applicants to Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo Consulates will pay more than the extra cost of $26.
For more information on the new procedure for the visa, visit the following page http:// mexico. usembassy/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.
