14 suspected drug traffickers arrested
A dozen searches have been carried out in Estrie Wednesday in the dismantling of a network of production and sale of cannabis.
Fourteen people have been arrested and face various charges.
Searches in Sherbrooke, Orford and Stoke, mostly in places that would have been used for the production of drugs.
" About 750 cannabis plants, four kilos of hashish, money and equipment for the production were seized ," reported Louis-Philippe Ruel, spokesman of the Safety of Quebec.
In all, eleven men and three women have been arrested, including the two alleged leaders of this network, two men of Sherbrooke.
The people arrested were due to appear in court Sherbrooke in the hours following their arrest.
They could face accusations of production of cannabis possession in traffic, conspiracy and theft of services, among others.
These searches took place in the investigation, which lasted almost a year.
" This information received from the public that has resulted in the arrests, said Mr. Ruel.
Some 70 regional module police investigation Estrie of the Safety of Quebec, Police Sherbrooke and police Memphrémagog, took part in the police operation.
