Rivières surveillance
Several rivers remain under scrutiny because of heavy rain that hit several areas of the province since Tuesday.
A landslide occurred Wednesday afternoon, Shawinigan, in Mauricie.
Two homes have been evacuated preventively.
In the evening, a shift occurred in Saint-Lin-Laurentides, in Lanaudière.
A road was collapsing.
From Tuesday to Wednesday evening, heavy rainfall hit several areas, or 40 to 70 mm of rain.
In 20 to 40 additional millimetres of rain were expected by Thursday evening, according to the regions.
The areas north of the river and in the Valley of the Outaouais were the most affected.
They could receive up to 100 mm of rain.
As it add these rainfall in the melting of the snow already accumulated in some sectors, there are fears the spillover of several rivers.
Warnings of flood warnings have been issued on Wednesday evening by the civil security of Quebec to rivers Ouareau and the Achigan, in Lanaudière.
The rivers North Saint-Jérôme, in the Laurentides, and the Chêne, in Lotbinière, showed that there were subject to flood vigils and remained under surveillance.
In Lanaudière, heavy rainfall led to glacial lakes, Sainte-Julienne, Sainte-Marcelline-de-Kildare as well as Rawdon.
In Saint-Calixte, a temporary bridge was taken because of heavy rain.
Ten homes had to be evacuated as a preventive measure.
In Outaouais, glacial lakes has led to the closing of several roads in the municipality of Mansfield-et-Pontefract.
The civil security remains on the same warning and is monitoring the situation closely, said Annik Bouchard, security adviser.
The Centre for flood forecasting Quebec has issued Wednesday, warnings of heavy flooding in several rivers, including Maskinongé, The Assumption, Ouareau, the Achigan, Batiscan and Loup.
