450 million in contracts without bidding
Quebec Hydroelectric has given over-the-counter $450 million in contracts for engineering firms for the hydroelectric project Eastmain-1-A-Sarcelle-Rupert.
At the heart of this avalanche of more than 100 contracts is a consortium of firms BPR, Dessau, SM and Axor has gained most important, the stewardship of the project, for a sum of $295 million without competitive bidding.
The consortium called Energy stewardship was formed in 2004 simultaneously in the choice of Quebec Hydroelectric to entrust the private sector its responsibility to manage this important project of $5 billion.
In early 2005, the Energy consortium managed were to pick up the lucrative contract without had a public tender.
For the Quebec, the use of consortia companies is a serious ethical problem that threatens to eliminate competition and drive up the price.
" This is the new way to collusion and to competition. "
" In other words, people, instead of making it so secret, now are doing so called ," said yesterday the Member péquiste Sylvain Simard in press conference.
earlier in the morning, Mr. Simard raised the issue in the National Assembly because it said see difficult to see how the public interest can be used in this way.
The minister of natural resources, Nathalie Normandeau, responded by afternoon, denying strongly that there has been collusion in the contract.
" I am beginning to get my journey ," she where after complaining that the PQ had been " dishonest " and had " lacked rigour ."
It said that " this is the least of the things that the PQ apologizes.
The consortia formula is a common practice in the world.
It is usually a limited alliance in the time allowed two or more companies to consolidate their respective expertise to meet a tender for a complex project.
The project Eastmain contains a high level of complexity given the scope of the work.
The construction is under way and must take until 2012.
, however, the contract was awarded without competition terms; there were negotiations.
So, consortia formula is no longer an exception in Quebec, even for relatively simple projects.
As revealed last week The Duty, consortia in génie-conseil made the subject of an investigation in government.
A rapid overview of the register of Quebec allows count over 200 consortia, some of which are permanent.
Thus, the firm Dessau works in partnership with most of its main competitors, including CIMA+, Génivar, SNC-Lavalin and other Roche and Tecsult.
Each combination, and there are tens, back to a single entity, or Dessau.
For Energy consortium stewardship, the Minister Normandeau stressed that " the territory of James Bay was dynamic of labour and that Quebec Hydroelectric does so special since the 1970s.
The leader of the project Eastmain, Réal Laporte, of the Society of energy James Bay (SEBJ -RRB - provided an explanation which has been hair on the fact that the concession contract was given over-the-counter.
" You in bidding and that there are few bidders, prices will be higher. "
" You have two choices: either you have the people who are in the market -là and you say: we will negotiate a satisfactory agreement and with a good price. "
