Even if they increase the consumption of products known as socially responsible in 2010, Quebecers appear to give very little credit to those who are trying to sell.
Two thirds of them say indeed believe the environmental commitment to business as the Green of companies, reveals the tool developed by the responsible consumption of the University Sherbrooke.
It half of consumers questioned the reliability of the official qualifications on the so-called fair, but also the credibility of products and brands being as being écoresponsables, said the Barometer.
In the same vein, the words of politicians on this theme is taken seriously by only 14.6 percent of Quebecers.
The information responsible consumption appears essential to stimulate this part of the lively consumption by almost one third of the Quebec consumers.
Indeed, the vacuum and the dubious nature of the information calmeraient restrain 46 per cent of consumers.
That is the second brake identified by the Barometer, after the higher price of these products.
