A global plan to renovate the lighting
The United Nations proposed yesterday to Cancún a renovation plan of the domestic, commercial and industrial lighting in 100 countries for a reduction of greenhouse gases (GHGs), which represents almost one third of the additional needed to stabilize the global climate by 2020.
The ambitious plan lies in the wake of major projects that the United Nations hopes in Cancún to compensate for the lack of binding commitments to reduce by industrialized countries.
Under the plan filed yesterday, if the incandescent light bulbs to monopolize still 50 to 70 per cent of the market were replaced by bulbs fluocompactes or, better, by light bulbs light-emitting diode (LED or LED in English -RRB - the bulk of 1.8 billion tons (GT) of GHG issued on the planet to enlighten people be avoided.
The lighting is responsible for 8 per cent of global emissions.
That is the equivalent of 70% of emissions of cars.
In Copenhagen, last year, the major emitters such as the United States, China, Europe and others, including Canada, have engaged in voluntary reduction plans that should increase aggregate GHG emissions of 53 gigatonnes by 49 gigatonnes.
But it from this assessment yet 5 Gt in order to stabilize by 2020 the rise of climate change to 2 degrees Celsius to avoid becoming out of control.
In the incandescent light bulbs, 95 percent of the energy is in the form of heat and the remaining 5% , of the light.
With bulbs fluocompactes, the energy expenditure is reduced by 75% and with the new bulbs LED, reduces the energy of two again.
The bulbs fluocompactes lasting an average of 6,000 to 10,000 hours.
The new bulbs LED, such as those that launched the manufacturing Philips this week - the company participated in the study - have a life expectancy of 25 000 and consume 80 percent less energy than a bulb smouldering fuse, which gives an idea of the economy with an alternative plan that would apply to 100 countries.
The new bulbs can also work with rhéostats in addition to making very little heat.
And they do not contain any mercury.
Several experts have posted reservations against bulbs fluocompactes because they contain mercury and that we must eliminate as hazardous waste, which is not always possible in developing countries, unless the manufacturing establish instructions.
, however, said the report, the main source of emissions of mercury on the planet is not the bulb fluocompacte, but rather the coal-fired power plants, which emit a lot of mercury to produce electricity wasted in the incandescent light bulbs.
In the United States alone, these plants emit 25 000 tonnes of mercury per year.
The report details the gains that each country would thanks to this programme.
For example, Indonesia sparing a billion dollars a year into electricity and eight million tonnes of CO2, or the equivalent of 3.5 plants whose construction cost 2.5 billion.
