The unemployment rate in France under the International Labour Office (ILO) remained at 9.3% in France (9.7 per cent in the overseas departments -RRB - show the seasonally adjusted (CVS) interim issued Thursday by INSEE.
The number of unemployed is 2.631 million in metropolis.
Data from the second quarter have been confirmed to 9.3% of the active population in France and 9.7% with the overseas territories.
In one year, the unemployment rate is rising 0.1 point.
More broadly, 3.4 million people in metropolitan France did not work in the third quarter but wanted to work, whether or not they are available in two weeks to work and that they are seeking a job.
youth situation on the labour market has deteriorated even further, with a further rise in the unemployment rate increased to 24.2% in France (+ 0.9 point in three months, +0.5 point on a year) and 25% including the overseas departments.
In the third quarter, 637 million young people aged 15 to 24 were unemployed in the ILO.
Senior citizens have experienced a slight rise in unemployment, to 6.4% in France (+0.2 point in three months and a year -RRB - or 482 million people aged 50 or over, and 6.6 per cent with the overseas departments.
Only 25 years have enjoyed stability of unemployment in the third quarter, to 8.3 per cent in France (-0.1 point in three months, an additional + 0.1 point on a year) and 8.8% in France.
