For more than ten months of July 2009 to May 2010, the fate of Clotilde Reiss, the young French researcher arrested in Iran on spying, the opinion in France, diplomacy, and increased the deterioration of relations between Paris and Tehran.
The everything under the watchful eyes of US diplomats.
The American documents obtained by WikiLeaks and consulted by Le Monde reveal some below this crisis.
They describe how the Élysée Palace has explained his strategy to the Americans, their advice for the treatment of their own crises of hostages in Iran (a small group of hikers).
They show how French officials have sought to convince Washington that the release of the young Frenchwoman had not been counterpart to the release of Majid Kakavand, an Iranian detained in France and wanted by the American justice for trafficking materials for the benefit of the Iranian nuclear programme.
Finally, they place in a harsh light the way in which the French Presidency has sought to manipulate the media to give credence to the idea that the Syrian president, Bashar al-Assad, played a central role in the release of Clotilde Reiss.
In reality, there was nothing.
diplomatic cable drafted the 12 August 2009 in Paris is entitled " Iran: French comments on how to deal with cases of hostages ."
