But his right arm, Gianni Letta, was " deeply concerned " by the market turmoil and a possible spillover from Ireland.
" The good news is that Italy, third economy of the euro zone, is not as Greece or Ireland. "
" The bad news is that it is as Portugal ," said Irwin Stelzer, economist at the Hudson Institute.
Clearly, his problem is the lack of growth and the sluggishness of tax revenue that goes with, making the state the risk of no longer being able to cover its funding needs.
The latest forecasts in Brussels have been a cold shower for the Government.
The Italian growth is now expected to 1.1 per cent in 2011 and 1.4 per cent in 2012. .. while the budget under consideration in the Senate panel on respectively 1.3% and 2% .
In these conditions, calculates the European Commission, the public deficit will still 4.3% of GDP next year, compared with 3.9 per cent forecast by the government) and 3.5 per cent in 2012 (instead of 2.7 per cent).
Hence the rumour of a new collective budget could be put in place after the holidays, for an amount of EUR 7 billion.
" If necessary, further austerity measures will be taken ," according to the Economic Affairs Commissioner Olli Rehn.
For the moment, Italy has the support of international institutions.
" The fundamentals of the economy are in order and its accounts are good, we repeat long has Karl Sadun, the Italian director at the International Monetary Fund in Italy at the IMF.
" There is no problem in the immediate, or the short or the long term, because despite its substantial debt (represented per cent of GDP in 2011, NDLR -RRB - requested stabilization efforts in Italy are lower than those proposed in other countries, " said Pier Carlo Padoan, chief economist of the OECD.
The question of political instability.
The 14 December, Silvio Berlusconi faces up to a motion of censure at the Chamber of Deputies, followed by elections could be held in late March.
With would open a period that decision-making in cases of serious crisis.
