Dry and ice: 24 departments in orange vigilance
The episodes snow still lead the traffic problems, including on the secondary network in Britain, and may disrupt economic activities.
Twenty-four departments are now vigilance orange because of the risk of snow and ice.
The Eure, the Eure-et-Loir, the Deux-Sèvres and Vienna, were added to the 20 departments already in orange vigilance, 18 since Wednesday afternoon and two, the Dordogne and the Gironde, later in the night.
According to Météo France, supported snow in the north of the Gironde and Charentes and snow low on the Ile de France.
layers of snow from 2 to 5 cm, on time of 7 to 10 cm, are expected for the departments concerned, and 1 to 3 cm, even up to 5 cm in the Paris region.
The departments concerned are those of the Charente, Charente-Maritime, Côtes of Armor, Finisterre, Gironde, Dordogne, Poitou and those regions Normandy, Ile-de-France and Limousin.
snow episodes are suffisament significant cause traffic problems and disrupt economic activities, warns Météo France.
In the Côtes of Armor, several departmental have been banned to lorries over 7.5 tonnes, whose Guingamp-Lannion and Saint-Brieuc-Loudéac.
The secondary movement on the network in Britain is very difficult in the gendarmes who recommend to take his vehicle in case of need and the movement of some buses TER was suspended for the day.
The school have been banned on Thursday in Picardy.
No specific measures were planned Wednesday evening to restrict the movement of vehicles.
The prefecture invites all motorists to exercise the utmost caution on the roads and to adjust their behaviour accordingly ."
The Department of Civil Aviation (DGAC) asked the airlines to cancel Thursday, 25 per cent of their flights on the Parisian Roissy airport and 10% to Orly because of snow ahead.
The DGAC recommends that air passengers to contact their airline.
In Britain, Gatwick airport south of London and Edinburgh, Scotland, are closed until Thursday morning.
