Hackers vengeful and diligence spies
The case WikiLeaks has a dual value.
On the one hand, it is a scandal, a scandal that is as scandal before the hypocrisy which governs relations between the Member States, citizens and the media.
On the other hand, it changes at international level, and suggests a future dominated by the regression.
But are in order.
The first aspect of WikiLeaks is confirmation that each file by secret service (of any nation) consists exclusively of press cuttings.
" extraordinary " American revelations on the sexual habits of Berlusconi only on what for months could be read in any newspaper (except those which Berlusconi owns -RRB - and the profile eerily caricature of Gaddafi was a cabaret artists substance to skit.
The rule that the secret files should be compounds that new already known is essential to the dynamic of the secret services, and not only in this century.
If you go into a bookshop of esoteric publications, you will see that each book repeat (on the Holy Grail, the mystery of Rennes-le-Château, followed or the Rose-Croix) exactly what was written in the previous books.
And not only because the author of hidden texts do not like the novel (or knows where to seek new on the non-existent -RRB - but because those involved in the occultisme believe what they already know, and reconfirms that they had already learned.
This is the mechanism of the success of Dan Brown.
Ditto for the secret files.
The informant is lazy, and lazy (or limited spirit), the head of the secret service (otherwise, it might be, that I do not know, editor of Liberation -RRB - which is as true as this.
The top secret on Berlusconi information that the US embassy in Rome was sending to the Department of State were the same as those that Newsweek published the week before.
So why the revelations on these cases have made much noise?
On the one hand, they say that any person cultivated already know, namely that the embassies, at least since the end of the Second World War, and since the Heads of States can telephone or take a plane to meet for dinner, have lost their diplomatic service and, with the exception of a few small exercises, turned into centres of espionage.
Any spectator film investigative knows very well that, and this is hypocrisy that one pretending to ignore.
However, repeat publicly violates the duty of hypocrisy, and put in a bad light American diplomacy.
Second, the idea that a hacker any can capture the secret more secrets of the most powerful country in the world is a significant blow to the prestige of the State Department.
The scandal does it not in crisis the victims and the perpetrators.
But the profound nature of what happened.
past, time of Orwell, could all power as a Big Brother who controlled every gesture of his subjects.
The Orwellian prophecy was completely been since, that can monitor each movement through telephone calls, each transaction, the hotel visited the motorway taken and the citizen became the victim of the eye of power.
But when, as now, that even the cryptes secrets of power cannot escape the clutches of a hacker, the monitoring report ceases to be unidirectional and is circular.
The power control each citizen, but each citizen, or at least the hacker - elected as vindictive citizen - can hear all the secrets of power.
How can a power which has the possibility to maintain its own secret can be taken?
It is true, Georg Simmel the true secret is a secret (and secret vacuum can never be unveiled); it is true, too, that knowing everything about the nature of Berlusconi or Merkel is indeed a secret empty secret, because public; but reveal, as did WikiLeaks, that the secret of Hillary Clinton were secret empty means it.
WikiLeaks has made no mistake to Sarkozy and Merkel, but has done too large to Clinton and Obama.
What will be the consequences of this wound to a very powerful power?
It is obvious that, in the future, states can no longer put online any privileged information - that would be to publish it on a poster on the street corner.
but it is equally clear that with the current technology, it is futile to hope to maintain confidential reports by telephone.
Nothing easier than to discover if and when a head of state has shifted in aircraft and contacted one of his colleagues.
How can be maintained in the future the private reports and reserved?
I know that, for the moment, my prediction is science fiction and is therefore romantic, but I am obliged to imagine government officials moving quietly in effort to uncontrollable routes, had been carrying messages learnt by heart or, at most, in hiding the rare information written in the heel of a shoe.
The information will be stored in single copy in drawers locked: basically, the attempt to espionage Watergate had less success that WikiLeaks.
I have had the opportunity to write that the technology is now in crabe, i.e. backwards.
A century after the Telegraph has revolutionized communications, Internet re-established a telegram on son (telephone).
cassettes (analogue) had made it possible for researchers in cinema to explore a film, going forward and back and see all the secrets of mounting, whereas now the CD (digital) can jump of chapter by chapter, i.e. macroportions.
With high-speed trains will be from Rome to Milan in three hours, whereas in aircraft, and that it includes requires three and a half hours.
It is not extraordinary that the political and communications in the cars.
One last comment.
the past, the press was trying to understand what went in the secret of embassies.
A far embassies that are confidential information to the press.
Weather: how France bidouille its promises of funding
A year after the Copenhagen Agreement, it is time to examine the promises of funding disbursed (so-called funding fast start or early) made by the developed countries.
And the big bidouillages French proved.
In the Copenhagen agreement, the developed countries pledged to provide $30 billion between 2010 and 2012.
The European Union has promised 7.2 billion euros over three years and France 1.26 billion (€ 420 million per year).
At the opening of the COP16, the EU has lifted the great game to persuade its partners in the reality of his commitment to funding fast start: report detailing its Member States press conference, great side event, distributing pamphlets. ..
The operation transparency is important and valued: developing countries and civil society would like all developed countries to do the same with the same level of precision.
The EU have emerged in 2010 2.2 billion euros, which puts it on the way to its commitment of 7.2 billion in 2012.
But when you look in detail, things are more complicated.
That money should be, according to the Copenhagen agreement, " new and additional " to ensure that an extra effort is made without being at the expense of ODA.
Unfortunately, there is no agreement on what " new and additional ."
While the European Commission had proposed a harmonization, some Member States, including France blocked the procedure.
Today, everyone chooses the reference that best suits.
The European Commission has, for example, be considered reference year 2009: international funding are maintained, and it would add 150 million three-year funding fast start.
Other countries have similar references in terms of year or in terms of the level of official development assistance.
By contrast, France believes that the funding of all new projects of the year 2010 are " new and additional ."
In other words, there is no reference to the previous years or at the global level of official development assistance.
Specifically, the total support of France to developing countries can remain stable (or even reduce -RRB - it claims to respect its commitment to funding new and additional ." ..
Another crucial element, the distribution of grants and loans.
Again, there is no rule and everyone chooses its calculation.
Some, such as France, consider that 1€ paid amounts to 1€.
Of course, it is hard to justify: the effort is not comparable.
If the use of loans can be justified for certain investments that are profitable (often projects related to the reduction of emissions based on more efficient technologies -RRB - it is a fallacy to submit a euro will recover as equivalent to a euro that. .. They should be counted under its commitments that the cost of the loan to the lender (the equivalent of an interest rate).
But France has to do with such reasoning: " respects " its commitment of 420 million euros in 91.5% of loans (389.8 million euros) and 8.5% of donations (36.1 million euros) - see the EU to check for yourself.
It is the only EU country to use if massive loan.
Germany is required to 46 per cent, while Denmark, the Netherlands and Slovakia (other) respect their commitments with 100% of donations.
In other words, when the vast majority of the European Union is 1€ to meet its commitment, France is only 10 cents and considers that the effort is comparable.
Joli sleight of hand.
In summary, in its financing fast start, France is a double fraud: on the action and the reality of the financial effort.
In spending that 36.1 million euros, it believe it spends 420 million new and additional " consistent with its promises.
The manipulation of the Ministry of Finance (because it appears that it is Bercy arbitration has done) could have a double negative impact, both in the EU (why the other Member States continue to give whether it is sufficient to pay?) and in the negotiations since developing countries are not completely fooled. ..
Chapter of early funding is only a small matter on short term, compared to the discussions on the climate.
But it could be a grain of sand in the vast machine that is the UNFCCC.
Let us hope that this is not the case.
In any case, it is essential to learn the lessons of this first year of funding early.
First, France could announce a change in its policy for the years 2011 and 2012, in a spirit of respect its commitments and equity with the other countries of the European Union.
Above all, France could move the discussion on the issues of long-term financing (other crucial chapter currently being discussed: it will not escape the question of " additionality " or policy loans.
France could change its position to become progressive on these issues it is on others.
The hope is based on the new Minister for the Environment, Mrs Kosciusko-Morizet, which will in Cancun next week.
A surprise announcement on the fast start of France and on its vision of additionality and the use of loans would increase the level of international confidence necessary for progress in the discussions.
Alert pesticides ingested by children
A 10-year-old child interfering in a day 81 different chemicals, according to a study published on Wednesday of the association Générations Futures (former Movement for Rights and respect for future generations).
The association, warned that its results were not significant statistical value in view of the low number of samples, but are illustrative of the issue addressed ," has purchased between July and September foods usually consumed in four meals and a encas in a day by a child of 10 years, in the Oise supermarkets and Paris.
These meals types, including the official recommendations - five fruits and vegetables, three dairy products and 1.5 litres of water a day, and sweets, were considered by research laboratories of chemicals, pesticides, heavy metals and other contaminants.
The base is damning: 81 chemicals, 42 of which are classified as carcinogenic possible or probable and five substances classified as carcinogens some and 37 substances that act as endocrine disruptors (PE -RRB - according to studies by several institutions such as the International Agency for Research on Cancer.
" Even if, in almost all cases, the legal limits for each chemical substance taken individually are not exceeded, it is clear in our survey that the reality of the exposure of consumers to possibly carcinogenic contaminants and/or EP is worrying ," notes the association.
For breakfast, butter and milk tea contain alone more than a dozen possible carcinogenic residues and three proven as carcinogenic some and nearly 20 residue that can disrupt the hormonal system.
The apple, imported from Brazil, planned as encas by the study, present traces of six chemicals including a fungicide yet banned in France.
Even to the green beans from Kenya, included in the lunch, on which the study detected traces of a powerful banned in the EU.
In addition, the burgers, the canned tuna, and even the wand of bread and the chewing gum were full of pesticides and other chemicals.
In the tap water analysis revealed the presence of nitrates and chloroform.
For dinner, the salmon steak was the " rich " with 34 chemical residues detected and even the base in plastic used to warm the food at the microwave was not free.
The final risk to consumers ' cocktails of contaminants " is probably underestimated ," according to the study.
The Alliance Europe Ecologie The Greens (EE-LV -RRB, for its part, has proposed " faced with the urgency of the situation " a moratorium on the use of pesticides, in order to stop " the increase in diseases of civilisation ."
In July, a study of the European agency for food safety (EFSA) reported the presence of residues of 365 different pesticides identified in fruit and vegetables consumed in Europe, 76 in cereals.
